\begin{document}$$ \frac{\partial\sigma_{\rm r}}{\partial{ r}}+\frac{2\sigma_{\rm r}}{r} -\frac{1}{r}(\sigma_{\rm l}+\sigma_{\rm c}) = 0 $$\end{document} where σr, σc, and σl denote the radial, circumferential and longitudinal component of the tissue stress tensor, respectively, and r indicates the radial position in the wall. We neglected shear stress components in view of the low shear stiffness of the tissue. The myocardial tissue was assumed to be incompressible, and to consist of myofibers, embedded in a collagen matrix. The Cauchy stress tensor
